sp_scores.title: Defeat Ushumgal without being KO'd.
Exploit Ushumgal's weakness to lightning attacks.

tip_battle.message: Melee attacks won't reach Ushumgal Subjugator, kupo! Use ranged attacks and lightning magic instead! And maybe even throw in some debuffs for good measure!
tip_battle.title: Ushumgal Subjugator

dungeons.epilogue: Lightning and Hope went underground to avoid the security net cast by PSICOM officer Rosch, but found themselves surrounded when they returned to the streets. They were rescued by Snow and Fang who appeared in the nick of time, summoning Shiva and scattering the soldiers. Snow learned that Hope was Nora's son, but just as Hope was planning to avenge his mother's death, a blast knocked the two of them to the ground.
dungeons.name: Palumpolum, Part 1
dungeons.prologue: Learning that l'Cie are hiding in the city of Palumpolum, Sanctum forces have called martial law into effect. Lightning's party lay low, preparing to infiltrate the capitol, Eden.

sp_scores.title: Exploit the Garuda Interceptor's weakness to wind attacks.

tip_battle.message: Garuda Interceptor is vulnerable to wind, kupo! But when its health gets low, watch out! It will become charged and use its Hellstorm Bolt ability, a lightning attack that hits the whole party! Use abilities like Power Break and Protect to take the edge off the damage!
tip_battle.title: Garuda Interceptor

dungeons.epilogue: Lightning and the others were shocked by the l'Cie brands that had appeared on them. As they fell from the Pulse Vestige, they saw a vision of Ragnarok attacking Cocoon, which Snow took as a sign they must defend it. Lightning refused to believe this, and accused Snow of siding with the fal'Cie that turned Serah to crystal. They later discovered Serah's crystal, and Snow decided to stay by her side and hold off the incoming PSICOM forces while Lightning and the rest pressed on.
dungeons.name: Lake Bresha 1
dungeons.prologue: Lightning and her party have fallen to Lake Bresha, a body of water turned to crystal by the magic of the fal'Cie Anima. Now branded l'Cie, they flee from their PSICOM pursuers.

sp_scores.title: Defeat Nix without being KO'd.

tip_battle.message: Stiria uses Doom at the start of the battle before bowing out and leaving you to fight Nix. Nix doesn't have any vulnerabilities, kupo, but she uses mostly physical attacks, so Power Break and Protect will reduce the damage coming in!
tip_battle.title: Nix and Stiria

dungeons.epilogue: As the light from Snow's l'Cie brand faded, the Shiva sisters appeared and laid waste to the PSICOM soldiers. They then turned their attention on Snow, sensing the doubt in him and wishing to test the worthiness of the one who had summoned them. Snow withstood their onslaught, and claimed their power as his own. Exhausted by the battle, he was approached by a mysterious l'Cie woman who ordered her troops to take him captive.
dungeons.name: Lake Bresha 2
dungeons.prologue: Unable to abandon Serah's crystal, Snow finds himself surrounded by PSICOM forces. As they close in, his l'Cie brand blazes with light...

sp_scores.title: Confuse Enki or Enlil.
Exploit Enki's weakness to lightning attacks.
Exploit Enlil's weakness to water attacks.

tip_battle.message: When Enki and Enlil get low on HP, they get really angry, kupo! Their attacks hit harder, but they also become vulnerable to Confuse! If that's not enough to turn the fight around, Enki is vulnerable to lightning, and Enlil is vulnerable to water, so hit 'em hard, kupo!
tip_battle.title: Enki & Enlil

dungeons.epilogue: Thinking to hide themselves in a crowd, Sazh and Vanille made for the city of Nautilus. With his son a Sanctum l'Cie and he himself a Pulse l'Cie, Sazh began to lose hope, while Vanille had to step into the rain to hide her own tears.
dungeons.name: Sunleth Waterscape
dungeons.prologue: Sazh and Vanille split from Lightning and flee through an uninhabited valley.

sp_scores.title: Exploit the Manasvin Warmech's weakness to lightning attacks.
Exploit the Manasvin Warmech's weakness to water attacks.

tip_battle.message: The Manasvin Warmech is vulnerable to lightning and water, kupo! It has a powerful group attack, though, so bring along someone with a Soul Break that can heal the entire party!
tip_battle.title: Manasvin Warmech

dungeons.epilogue: Lightning's assault derailed the train, plunging everything around her into chaos. She and Sazh battled their way through Sanctum forces towards the center of the battlefield, defeating the unrelenting Manasvin Warmech along the way. Sazh had thought Lightning was one of the Sanctum soldiers, leaving him puzzled why she would oppose the Purge. She quipped that she wasn't a soldier anymore, and pressed onward...
dungeons.name: The Hanging Edge
dungeons.prologue: Under rule of the Sanctum, the people of Cocoon knew peace and prosperity. The story of this realm begins as a train carrying Lightning speeds towards the Hanging Edge...

sp_scores.title: Afflict the Dreadnought with Blind.

tip_battle.message: The Dreadnought periodically checks itself for debuffs and uses Steam Clean to get rid of them. Use attacks that inflict debuffs to trigger its cleaning mode, then move in for the kill while it's busy steaming, kupo!
tip_battle.title: Dreadnought

dungeons.epilogue: There was a rift in Lightning's party and they split into two groups. Hope was amazed to learn that Lightning risked her life to save her sister Serah by boarding a Purge train. Tired of babysitting Hope, Lightning left him behind, though he soon met up with Sazh and Vanille. They eventually caught up with Lightning, but were thrown into combat against Dreadnought, a Pulse automata. They emerged victorious, but Sazh and Vanille chose to withdraw, while Lightning and Hope continued their journey.
dungeons.name: The Vile Peaks 1
dungeons.prologue: Though Lightning and her companions managed to escape aboard an airship, their victory is short-lived, as PSICOM shoots them down over the Vile Peaks. Undaunted, Lightning and her companions press on...

sp_scores.title: Defeat Ushumgal without being KO'd.
Exploit Ushumgal's weakness to lightning attacks.

tip_battle.message: This time around melee attacks WILL reach Ushumgal Subjugator! Whomever it locks on to will take a shower of punishing attacks, so watch out, kupo! Keep that character healed while you lash out with lightning attacks to punish its weakness!
tip_battle.title: Ushumgal Subjugator

sp_scores.title: Defeat the Havoc Skytank without being KO'd.

tip_battle.message: Havoc Skytank is in the sky, kupo, so melee attacks won't reach it! Aim for the 4 turrets and hulls--when they go down, they deal huge damage to the Skytank itself! Use summons and magic that hits all enemies at once to bring it crashing down!
tip_battle.title: Havoc Skytank

dungeons.epilogue: The party regrouped at the Estheim Residence, where Hope backed down from his plans for vengeance against Snow after Snow risked everything to protect him. Hope's father Bartholomew, too, showed no change in his affection for his son, even now that Hope was a l'Cie. Though they were attacked while at the Residence, Cavalry soldiers intervened, helping them to break free. Thus did Hope say farewell to his father and begin a new journey.
dungeons.name: Palumpolum, Part 2
dungeons.prologue: Lightning is reassured after learning that Fang and Vanille awoke in Cocoon after being in crystal stasis for centuries. They move to regroup at the Estheim Residence.

tip_battle.title: Nix and Stiria

sp_scores.title: Defeat Odin without being KO'd.

tip_battle.message: Odin is a powerful enemy with a variety of attacks, and no real vulnerabilities. Defensive abilities like Power Break and Protectga come highly recommended in this fight, kupo!
tip_battle.title: Odin

dungeons.epilogue: Together, Lightning and Hope defeated Odin, and after the battle Lightning noticed her l'Cie brand had changed. Lightning apologized to Hope for getting angry at him, and allowed him to stay with her on her journey. Meanwhile Snow was still being held captive by the l'Cie Fang and the Cavalry, where he learned of the plan to execute the Pulse l'Cie.
dungeons.name: The Vile Peaks 2
dungeons.prologue: As Lightning and Hope move forward, Lightning grows increasingly convinced that Hope is only slowing her down, and in her anger she summons Odin...

sp_scores.title: Exploit the Aster Protoflorian's window of weakness to fire attacks.
Exploit the Aster Protoflorian's window of weakness to ice attacks.
Exploit the Aster Protoflorian's window of weakness to lightning attacks.

tip_battle.message: Every few turns Aster Protoflorian changes forms, and its elemental weakness and resistance changes with it! It always changes in the same order though, kupo, so pay attention, and get it on the back foot--er, tentacle, kupo!
tip_battle.title: Aster Protoflorian

dungeons.epilogue: In his travels with Lightning, Hope learned the origin of Snow's resistance group NORA and told Lightning that his mother's death was Snow's fault. Hope swears he will grow strong enough to take his revenge, but Lightning worries that his course of action will only cause more suffering.
dungeons.name: Gapra Whitewood
dungeons.prologue: As they make their way through the military's Ecological Research Zone, Lightning helps her companion Hope navigate his conflicted emotions.
